  "note": "Covers all 95 Virginia counties plus the 28 independent cities that elect their own sheriff (123 sheriff jurisdictions), per the Virginia Sheriffs' Association directory (Nov 2025); VA sheriffs were elected Nov-2023 for four-year terms beginning Jan-2024, with mid-term vacancies filled by appointment/special election (Grayson: Gary C. Hash took office 01/01/2026; Hanover: Gregory W. Six 04/01/2026; Emporia: Dameon White 07/01/2025; Wythe: Anthony R. Cline 08/01/2025); three cities share a jointly-elected sheriff folded into the county entry (Covington with Alleghany County, Poquoson with York County, Williamsburg with James City County), and seven grandfathered second-class cities have no separate sheriff, sharing constitutional officers with an adjacent county (Fairfax City with Fairfax County, Franklin with Southampton, Galax with Carroll/Grayson, Harrisonburg with Rockingham, Lexington with Rockbridge, Manassas and Manassas Park with Prince William); no jurisdictions were left unfilled."
